      "target": {
        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "ci: add GitHub Pages deploy workflow for website",
        "body": "## Summary\r\n\r\n- Adds `.github/workflows/deploy-website.yml` to build and deploy the `website/` directory to GitHub Pages on every push to `main` that touches `website/**`\r\n- Builds with `VITE_BASE=/vox/` so Vite generates asset paths rooted at `steipete.github.io/vox/`\r\n- Uses `actions/upload-pages-artifact@v3` + `actions/deploy-pages@v4` in a two-job pipeline (build → deploy) with the `pages` concurrency group to prevent overlapping deployments\r\n\r\n## Required one-time setup\r\n\r\nBefore the first deploy can run, a repo admin must enable Pages in:\r\n**Settings → Pages → Source → GitHub Actions**\r\n\r\n## Notes\r\n\r\nThe `website/vite.config.ts` base-path change (`base: process.env.VITE_BASE ?? \"/\"`) is part of the `fix/truncate-audio-bounds` PR and must land on `main` alongside the website source for the deploy to produce correct asset URLs. This workflow file can merge in any order — it will simply wait for the next `website/**` push to trigger.\r\n\r\n## Test plan\r\n\r\n- [ ] Enable Pages source in repo settings (Settings → Pages → GitHub Actions)\r\n- [ ] Merge `fix/truncate-audio-bounds` (brings `website/` + `vite.config.ts` base-path fix)\r\n- [ ] Confirm workflow triggers and site is live at `https://steipete.github.io/vox/`\r\n\r\n",
        "branch": "chore/github-pages-deploy",
